{"id":"12478","name":"Mr. Link","tagline":"Returns with a shareable link or QR code for your file","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g59718","latest":"34008","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Mr. Link</h1>\n<p>iOS and macOS </p>\n<p>.  .  .  .  .  .</p>\n<p>This is a simple shortcut I made using the getfile.io api because I have issues getting similar existing shortcuts to work for me.</p>\n<p>It takes any file you give it and returns with the option to open the download link, copy it, create a QR code that saves to your photos, or “share…” which opens the share sheet and allows you to share the download link directly. </p>\n<p>You can share your file to the shortcut via the share sheet, otherwise if there’s no input, it will prompt you to select a file. </p>\n<p><em>Please let me know if anything needs updating, as getfile’s api is currently in beta.</em> </p>\n<p>ko-fi: ctzndwn<br>\nReddit: citizendown<br>\nDiscord: ctzndwn#3339</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - July 5, 2022, 6:52 a.m.</strong></p>"}